    • Method Detail

      • compareUniqueMode

        public static void compareUniqueMode(ArrayList<VDataObjectValueArray> arrs,
                                     Instant time,
                                     int[] result)
        Compare time to object list's times. The object list is sorted. If there is a matching time, return its position; otherwise return an appropriate position for insert. The compare result will be stored in the passed-in result array. Array's first item is the found index, the second item is whether at the position is a matching time or not.
        Parameters:
        arrs - a list of object value arrays
        time - the time to compare
        result - to store compare results in this array

      • compareAllMode

        public static void compareAllMode(ArrayList<VDataObjectValueArray> arrs,
                                  Instant time,
                                  DExpand expand,
                                  Integer colidx,
                                  String[] subNames,
                                  Integer[] subIndices,
                                  int[] result)
        Compare time to object list's times. The object list is sorted. If there is a matching time, return its position; otherwise return an appropriate position for insert. The compare result will be stored in the passed-in result array. Array's first item is the found index, the second item is whether at the position is a matching time or not.
        Parameters:
        arrs - the list of object arrays
        time - the time to compare
        expand - the column expand mode
        colidx - the index of the column
        subNames - the names of the child columns of complex type
        subIndices - the indices of the child columns of complex type
        result - the compare results
